---
// Privacy & Site Policy page — Cotton background, Noir text
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/navigation/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/navigation/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy & Site Policy"
  description="Ncheta Magazine — documenting African art narratives, from historical scholarship to the contemporary market."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <article class="prose-content">
      <header class="mb-10">
        <!-- Breadcrumb -->
        <nav
          class="mb-8 font-inter text-xs text-noir/40 flex gap-2"
          aria-label="Breadcrumb"
        >
          <a href="/" class="transition-colors">Home</a>
          <span>/</span>
          <span class="text-noir/60">Privacy & Site Policy</span>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="font-cinzel font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-noir mb-3">
          Privacy & Site Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xs text-noir/40 font-inter">
          Last updated: <time datetime="2026-07-22">July 22, 2026</time>
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <p>
          Ncheta Magazine receives, collects and stores information and Personal
          Data — hereinafter ‘PD’ — entered or provided by the website user of
          www.nchetamagazine.com. We respect your privacy and attach great
          importance to the respect and protection of your PD. Further, we
          collect the Internet Protocol address — hereinafter ‘IP’ — used to
          connect your computer to the internet. We may use software tools to
          measure and collect session information, including page response
          times, length of visits to certain pages, page interaction
          information, and methods used to browse away from the page. When you
          conduct a transaction on our website, as part of the process, we
          collect personal information you give us such as your name, address
          and email address. Your personal information will be used for the
          specific reasons stated above only.
        </p>
        <p>
          We collect such Non-personal and Personal Information for the
          following purposes: (i) to provide and operate the services; (ii) to
          provide our users with ongoing customer assistance and technical
          support; (iii) to be able to contact our visitors and users with
          general or personalized service-related notices and promotional
          messages; (iv) to create aggregated statistical data and other
          aggregated and/or inferred non-personal Information, which we or our
          business partners may use to provide and improve our respective
          services; (v) to comply with any applicable laws and regulations.
        </p>
        <p>
          We may contact you to notify you regarding your account, to
          troubleshoot problems with your account, to resolve a dispute, to
          collect fees or monies owed, to poll your opinions through surveys or
          questionnaires, to send updates about our company, or as otherwise
          necessary to contact you to enforce our User Agreement, applicable
          national laws, and any agreement we may have with you. For these
          purposes we may contact you via email, telephone, text messages, and
          postal mail.
        </p>
        <blockquote
          class="italic text-noir/65 bg-noir/5 p-5 border-l-2 border-cherry my-8 font-inter text-sm leading-relaxed"
        >
          We reserve the right to modify this privacy policy at any time, so
          please review it frequently. Changes and clarifications will take
          effect immediately upon their posting on the website. If we make
          material changes to this policy, we will notify you here that it has
          been updated, so that you are aware of what information we collect,
          how we use it, and under what circumstances, if any, we use and/or
          disclose it.
        </blockquote>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2>Website Disclaimer & User Agreement</h2>
        <p>
          By using www.nchetamagazine.com, users agree to the terms of use and
          privacy policy of Ncheta Magazine, including the selected cookie
          settings in order to improve your online experience and to keep track
          of statistical data.
        </p>
        <p>
          We attach great importance and attention to the correctness of the
          provided information. However, despite efforts, Ncheta Magazine cannot
          guarantee that the provided information is complete, correct or
          accurate. In addition, Ncheta Magazine can change, adjust, delete or
          update any information and text without prior notice. The content on
          this website is not subject to official character. If the information
          on the website is incorrect, we will make every effort in order to
          rectify this problem as soon as possible. Furthermore, concerning
          technical interruptions or problems, however we are not responsible
          for the inaccessibility of www.nchetamagazine.com, nor guarantee that
          it is free of technical faults, Ncheta Magazine promises to make every
          effort to prevent these inconveniences.
        </p>
        <p>
          When being confronted with inaccuracies or technical problems, please
          notify our editors by mailing to <a
            href="mailto:hello@nchetamagazine.com">hello@nchetamagazine.com</a
          >. From a legal perspective, Ncheta Magazine cannot be held liable for
          direct or indirect damage resulting from the use of the website or the
          information and content available on — or via — the website.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>The links to other websites published on </strong> www.nchetamagazine.com
          are outside of the control of Ncheta Magazine. Therefore, we cannot be held
          responsible for the substantive value of these links, nor for their technical
          functioning, availability or the completeness of the information sources
          and websites provided. As a result, Ncheta Magazine accepts no liability
          for direct or indirect damages resulting from the consultation or use of
          such external websites and content.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
